{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","title":"overlayBounds","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","title":"overlayBounds","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"role":"symbol","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNOverlay","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"}}}